summary: Tony, pulling Peter aside: Don’t tell your Father, but I threw out his pie for the store bought one so he doesnt get hurt...
body:
Tony, pulling Peter aside: Don’t tell your Father, but I threw out his pie for the store bought one so he doesnt get hurt feelings when everyone says it taste bad.

Peter, frowning: I made that pie though…

Tony: oh sweetie, it taste like bear shit. You can’t bake.
